<br>
I had 3 idiots the other day complaining that I stole their camp.  I log on, walk over to the flies camp in PoD.  Call out the usual camp check.  Full pop, nobody claiming...I start killing.  Suddenly 2 toons sit a bit back, and one of em sends me a tell &quot;We'll let you kill a few more while we med, then we'll take our camp back&quot;.  WFT???  He then tells me they left to go pick up fresh KEI (they did have a lvl 5X chanter, but we all know C2 doesn't work anymore, right?).<br>
<br>
Of course I tell em to go to hunt somewhere else, they lost their camp.  My thinking being &quot;No, it's my camp, I was here this morning.  I just had to leave quick to go wash the dog, mow the lawn, change a diaper and do my wife&quot;, but I settle for just, &quot;you left, I was free, it's mine now&quot;.<br>
<br>
So then the idiots proceed to start pulling my mobs (they had 1 melee, 1 druid, 1 enc) using 2 charmed pets.  Deciding I need to protect my turf, I issue a warning that I'm gonna dispel the pets to one of em.  They keep going...I dispel.  Crying ensues, and they complain more (think one died).  So they spend the next 20 mins dispelling my pet, and mobs I snare and root.  Being a druid, it's no biggie, I just refresh, run around, etc till they get tired, or the GM I petitioned for shows up.  They left first...<br>
<br>
Morals of this story:<br>
<br>
1- If you leave a camp for any reason, you stand to have it taken by someone else.  Needing KEI is not a valid excuse.  Going LD is about only one!<br>
<br>
2- Nice to be able to dispel pets (knowing it's an offense) and don't care about being banned cause you're playing just until your account expires anyways.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I woudn't do it just to bug others, but I will protect my camps!<br>
