<br>
What really fries my butt are the children who tell you, when you tell them politely that useless_mob_1 is camped, that there is no such thing as camping in EQ.  Yeah, and there is no law requiring you to say please or thank you, but it's common courtesy and convention, and honoring camps is the same thing.  I understand why Verant doesn't want to make camping an official part of the rules, but it still seems to me that &quot;play nice&quot; should include respecting the rights of the first person there.    <br>
<br>
KEI = bad for EQ.  Casters have always had an advantage over melees, KEI takes that advantage and magnifies it several times.  KEI means almost no down time, you can chain kill whites and even sometimes yellows all the way into your 40s.  No melee can do that, even a fungi tunic is not as good for melees as KEI is for casters. <br>
<br>
And then there are the casters who claim they can't play without KEI.  Wrong.  Of course you can play without KEI, you'd just have lots of downtime if you solo, and you'd have to be more judicious about use of mana in a group.  I play my shammy without KEI all the time, and it sucks when he's low on mana and is being asked for all the shammy buffs, but I can do all of the mission critical stuff that I need to do without constant KEI, and without absurd downtime.  If I can't do the &quot;nice to have&quot; buffs, and if I can't buff everyone in the group, well that's just the way it is.  <br>
<br>
/rant off <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xlabikxbonekissah>Xlabikx Bonekissah</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.flamingtext.com/clipart/fontart/gen/fred/A.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/14/03 2:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3169.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hmmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No begging needed Xlapnut, there is always a crack ho in Nexus. You just hand in a few pp and you're set for 4 hours. Yes, necros dont need KEI, but who gives a f*ck?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
